commitResults.messageTitle: Add filter command to filter persons by tags
commitResults.messageBody:
- Implement `FilterCommand` to allow users to filter persons by
their tags.
- Add `TagContainsKeywordsPredicate` to handle the filtering logic
by comparing tags with the keywords provided.
- Implement `FilterCommandParser` to parse user input and create
a `FilterCommand`.
- Update `AddressBookParser` to recognize and dispatch the
`filter` command.
- Ensure tag comparison is case-insensitive and handles multiple
tags.

How it works:
- The `filter` command allows users to search for contacts by
their tags.
- If the user provides multiple keywords (e.g., `filter friend
colleague clown`), it will return all contacts that have any
of the specified tags.
- The search is case-insensitive, so tags like `FRIEND`
or `Clown` will still match `friend` or `clown`.

commitResults.messageTitle: Enforce spouse role validation in Wedding class
commitResults.messageBody:
- Added `isSpouse` method in the Wedding class to check if
a person is the designated husband or wife.
- Added `addRoleToMap` method in the Wedding class to
ensure that a spouse cannot be assigned additional roles in the ContactMap.
- Kept the ContactMap class unaware of the husband and wife
to avoid unnecessary coupling and maintain separation between client and vendor roles.
- Improved validation logic by centralizing spouse checks within
the Wedding class, maintaining a clean separation of responsibilities.
